  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GWFP Phoenix/BNP</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The most significant expected development impacts include: (i) increased access for Phoenix to trade finance to support the growth of sourcing, trading and distribution of rice, pulses, grains and sugar into Asia &amp; Sub-Saharan Africa, hence promoting food security in several IDA countries; (ii) increased farmers reach by providing a sizable and stable source of financing for Phoenix&apos;s purchase of agri commodities mainly from small and medium-sized farmers, and (iii) indirect support to the business of companies involved in import/export, transportation, storage, distribution of agri commodities, which is expected to sustain employment along the value chain.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project consists of an investment by IFC of up to US$20 million in a revolving uncommitted trade finance facility of US$80 million (the Facility), arranged by BNP Paribas (Suisse) S.A. (BNPP Suisse) for Phoenix Global DMCC (Phoenix DMCC), a subsidiary of Phoenix Commodities Pvt. Ltd (Phoenix). The Facility will support Phoenixs fast-growing agri commodity supply chain business in Africa and other regions.</narrative>
  </description>
